@page "/about"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<h2 class="text-center text-primary mb-4">About EventEase</h2>

<div class="card shadow-lg mx-auto" style="max-width: 700px;">
    <div class="card-body">

        <p class="fs-5">
            <strong>EventEase</strong> is a modern, interactive web application built with <strong>Blazor (.NET 8)</strong>.
            It's designed to simplify the event experience whether you're organizing, exploring, or registering.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h5>🛠️ Features</h5>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
            <li class="list-group-item">View upcoming events with sleek card layouts</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Explore rich event details with intuitive navigation</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Quick registration with validation and smooth feedback</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Responsive design for desktop and mobile</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>🌐 Tech Stack</h5>
        <p>
            EventEase is powered by <strong>Blazor Web Apps</strong> using:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>.NET 8 and Razor components</li>
            <li>Bootstrap 5 for styling</li>
            <li>JavaScript interop for client-side alerts</li>
            <li>Mock services for simulated data flow</li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h5>👨‍💻 Developer Insight</h5>
        <p>
            This project reflects a journey of resilience, debugging triumphs, and continuous improvement.
            From cracking binding issues to redesigning clean UX flows, every feature was earned through hands-on persistence.
        </p>

        <p class="fst-italic text-muted">
            EventEase: not just another app  it’s a growth story written in code.
        </p>

        <div class="d-flex justify-content-end mt-4">
            <a href="/events" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Back to Events</a>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

